1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,419
<i>And you dare call me--</i>

2
00:00:02,502 --> 00:00:04,170
<i>Then, prove you're not a coward.</i>

3
00:00:04,921 --> 00:00:07,424
<i>- Face me.</i>
<i>- Oh, I'm definitely going to face you.</i>

4
00:00:09,592 --> 00:00:12,971
<i>Help me protect my</i>
<i>brother from your insane father!</i>

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:16,349
<i>Edong, if you have Mel,</i>
<i>Please, I'm begging you, don't hurt her.</i>

6
00:00:16,433 --> 00:00:17,684
<i>Don't worry.</i>

7
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:21,855
<i>Soon enough… everything will blow up.</i>

8
00:00:22,856 --> 00:00:24,983
<i>- Everyone, out!</i>
<i>- It's an emergency!</i>

9
00:00:25,066 --> 00:00:29,195
<i>Go to the fire exit! Move! Move!</i>

10
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:35,660
[suspenseful music playing]

11
00:00:47,297 --> 00:00:49,132
[bomb technician] <i>Sir, negative for IED!</i>

12
00:00:49,632 --> 00:00:50,842
<i>But there's a hand in here.</i>

13
00:00:51,384 --> 00:00:52,552
<i>It's Mel's?</i>

14
00:00:52,635 --> 00:00:53,636
<i>Mel!</i>

15
00:00:54,220 --> 00:00:55,221
<i>Mel!</i>

16
00:00:58,600 --> 00:00:59,684
<i>Hey.</i>

17
00:01:00,101 --> 00:01:02,020
<i>Isn't that my missing backpack, Lucas?</i>

18
00:01:02,771 --> 00:01:04,272
<i>Did your brother steal that?</i>

19
00:01:04,355 --> 00:01:06,232
<i>I'm sure his underwear's stolen, too.</i>

20
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:07,692
<i>- For sure.</i>
<i>- Hi!</i>

21
00:01:08,568 --> 00:01:11,237
<i>Bullying people doesn't make you cute.</i>

22
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:12,614
<i>You know that, right?</i>

23
00:01:18,036 --> 00:01:19,412
<i>They'll stop eventually.</i>

24
00:01:19,871 --> 00:01:21,414
<i>Why are you letting them bully you?</i>

25
00:01:21,831 --> 00:01:24,626
<i>I can't let them affect me, or I'll lose.</i>

26
00:01:24,709 --> 00:01:26,836
[soft music playing]

27
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:30,799
<i>Ah, your mom worked for</i>
<i>my family when we were young.</i>

28
00:01:31,466 --> 00:01:33,927
<i>And you've been to our house before.</i>

29
00:01:34,302 --> 00:01:35,428
<i>Do you remember?</i>

30
00:01:37,514 --> 00:01:38,473
<i>Yeah.</i>

31
00:01:40,183 --> 00:01:41,726
<i>Uh, wait.</i>

32
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:44,813
<i>Are you in a rush?</i>
<i>Or looking for something?</i>

33
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:48,358
[soft music continues]

34
00:01:54,364 --> 00:01:56,032
<i>Do you have your gifts ready?</i>

35
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:57,492
<i>I still don't have mine.</i>

36
00:01:57,575 --> 00:02:00,036
<i>Why don't we just give her a group gift?</i>

37
00:02:00,120 --> 00:02:02,122
<i>Erica deserves to get a lot of gifts.</i>

38
00:02:02,205 --> 00:02:04,624
<i>- Her mom won't get her any.</i>
- [chuckles]

39
00:02:04,707 --> 00:02:07,001
<i>I reminded you about this last week.</i>

40
00:02:07,085 --> 00:02:08,378
<i>Then, I'm sorry.</i>

41
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:11,131
<i>Just help me find a gift for her.</i>

42
00:02:11,673 --> 00:02:13,007
<i>What would she like?</i>

43
00:02:13,091 --> 00:02:14,884
<i>A dress? A bag?</i>

44
00:02:16,469 --> 00:02:17,554
<i>A boyfriend…</i>

45
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:20,765
<i>A boyfriend? For Erica?</i> [chuckles]

46
00:02:24,144 --> 00:02:28,148
[unsettling music plays]

47
00:02:29,190 --> 00:02:31,776
<i>I shouldn't have told</i>
<i>you about my issue with Edong.</i>

48
00:02:32,777 --> 00:02:34,362
<i>I didn't know this would happen.</i>

49
00:02:35,363 --> 00:02:38,032
<i>I'm sorry, too. I should've told you.</i>

50
00:02:39,450 --> 00:02:41,286
<i>I'll introduce you to Lucas.</i>

51
00:02:41,369 --> 00:02:44,497
<i>I promise, he's not bad at all.</i>

52
00:02:49,752 --> 00:02:51,004
[music fades]

53
00:02:51,087 --> 00:02:52,714
[Annette] <i>The calls I keep getting!</i>

54
00:02:53,965 --> 00:02:58,469
<i>Everyone's assuming we're the reason</i>
<i>why Louisa's case is still open.</i>

55
00:03:00,638 --> 00:03:03,057
<i>If all evidences point to Edong,</i>

56
00:03:03,141 --> 00:03:04,726
<i>that only means one thing.</i>

57
00:03:04,809 --> 00:03:07,270
<i>They have the right guy!</i>

58
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:09,188
<i>So, the next time the cops call,</i>

59
00:03:09,272 --> 00:03:11,900
<i>just tell them what they want.</i>

60
00:03:12,317 --> 00:03:16,529
<i>But they want us to say</i>
<i>that we saw Edong in the scene.</i>

61
00:03:16,946 --> 00:03:18,531
<i>Like I said,</i>

62
00:03:19,073 --> 00:03:21,701
<i>just give them what they want!</i>

63
00:03:21,784 --> 00:03:25,413
<i>Mel, we have suffered enough.</i>

64
00:03:25,830 --> 00:03:27,457
<i>Let's put an end to this nonsense now!</i>

65
00:03:28,416 --> 00:03:30,919
<i>- But Dad…</i>
<i>- Didn't I tell you?</i>

66
00:03:31,002 --> 00:03:33,296
<i>I told you not to be friends with them!</i>

67
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:35,798
<i>But what? Did you listen?</i>

68
00:03:35,882 --> 00:03:38,176
<i>Now, look at what</i>
<i>we all have to go through!</i>

69
00:03:41,221 --> 00:03:43,723
<i>Even with your choice of friends,</i>

70
00:03:43,806 --> 00:03:46,226
<i>you are a disappointment!</i>

71
00:03:47,185 --> 00:03:48,603
<i>Now, fix this!</i>

72
00:03:53,858 --> 00:03:59,530
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
dark instrumental playing]

73
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:20,677
["Sabay Sabay Tayo"
dark instrumental continues]

74
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:26,182
<i>It's Louisa's watch.</i>

75
00:04:27,267 --> 00:04:31,271
[music turns haunting]

76
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:43,574
[theme music playing]

77
00:05:57,732 --> 00:06:01,235
[Erica] <i>Mel! Mel! It's Mel!</i>

78
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:05,281
<i>Edong told me he'd</i>
<i>shown Mel what justice means.</i>

79
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:07,742
[somber music playing]

80
00:06:07,825 --> 00:06:10,745
[Edong] <i>I know now what I can achieve.</i>

81
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:15,249
<i>I know now what I need to do.</i>

82
00:06:16,292 --> 00:06:18,086
<i>All because of them.</i>

83
00:06:18,544 --> 00:06:20,755
<i>"Them"? Who's them?</i>

84
00:06:20,838 --> 00:06:23,800
[Edong] <i>The people who put me in jail.</i>

85
00:06:23,883 --> 00:06:25,301
[Lucas] <i>Are you going to punish them?</i>

86
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:27,220
[Edong] <i>Not at all.</i>

87
00:06:28,054 --> 00:06:29,764
<i>I'll help them.</i>

88
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:33,434
<i>I'll help them fix their mistakes.</i>

89
00:06:33,976 --> 00:06:38,147
<i>I'll show them what a real criminal is.</i>

90
00:06:38,940 --> 00:06:40,775
<i>They need to experience it for themselves.</i>

91
00:06:40,858 --> 00:06:43,653
<i>They need to suffer!</i>

92
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:47,907
[somber music continues]

93
00:06:53,996 --> 00:06:57,208
<i>Are you still mad at</i>
<i>me for choosing Anton?</i>

94
00:06:58,334 --> 00:07:00,002
<i>I meant what I said before.</i>

95
00:07:00,795 --> 00:07:02,964
<i>Ending our relationship</i>
<i>was the right thing to do.</i>

96
00:07:03,965 --> 00:07:05,299
<i>You did it for your child.</i>

97
00:07:05,383 --> 00:07:07,718
<i>But I lost the baby, anyway.</i>

98
00:07:09,178 --> 00:07:12,849
[Mel] <i>I should've left him and chose you.</i>

99
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:18,813
[grunts]

100
00:07:21,732 --> 00:07:24,318
[somber music fades]

101
00:07:24,402 --> 00:07:26,404
We've had the security check the CCTV.

102
00:07:27,530 --> 00:07:30,867
The rider who delivered
the package had his face covered.

103
00:07:31,909 --> 00:07:34,787
He was also not
wearing a uniform, so I think…

104
00:07:35,788 --> 00:07:37,248
[sighs] …someone else sent him.

105
00:07:38,082 --> 00:07:41,002
The crime ops said
they just need a little time

106
00:07:41,085 --> 00:07:43,671
to get the fingerprint identification.

107
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:46,883
They said they got good prints

108
00:07:46,966 --> 00:07:50,845
because the driver wasn't wearing gloves.

109
00:07:53,973 --> 00:07:55,975
I'll go call your friends.

110
00:07:57,977 --> 00:07:59,103
I'll do it.

111
00:08:00,021 --> 00:08:01,939
Even Mel's husband and family?

112
00:08:09,489 --> 00:08:13,075
[exhales heavily] Let's just wait for
the results from the crime ops.

113
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:18,080
Shit.

114
00:08:18,789 --> 00:08:19,832
My keys.

115
00:08:21,584 --> 00:08:23,085
I have a duplicate, remember?

116
00:08:24,253 --> 00:08:25,254
[sighs]

117
00:08:26,672 --> 00:08:27,632
Thanks.

118
00:08:29,342 --> 00:08:30,885
[woman] Do you need help?

119
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:33,930
With packing up?

120
00:08:34,013 --> 00:08:36,974
After what happened earlier,
you should be leaving.

121
00:08:37,475 --> 00:08:38,476
[huffs]

122
00:08:38,559 --> 00:08:41,270
Hello? Are you listening to me?

123
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:44,315
Ma'am, we all had a long night.

124
00:08:44,398 --> 00:08:47,610
If you need anything,
can you just tell us tomorrow?

125
00:08:47,693 --> 00:08:48,945
[scoffs] Tomorrow?

126
00:08:49,028 --> 00:08:51,113
I didn't graduate from
a prestigious university,

127
00:08:51,197 --> 00:08:53,491
became the best
employee at a global company,

128
00:08:53,574 --> 00:08:57,370
to buy this condo unit,
just to die from a bomb explosion.

129
00:08:58,412 --> 00:09:02,124
Attorney, we have nothing
to do with your righteous crusades.

130
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:03,751
[Erica exhales sharply]

131
00:09:03,834 --> 00:09:09,257
[tense music playing]

132
00:09:20,977 --> 00:09:22,311
[sighs heavily]

133
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,981
[music fades]

134
00:09:25,064 --> 00:09:27,817
Okay, Uncle.
I'll update you straight away.

135
00:09:31,445 --> 00:09:32,488
[sighs deeply]

136
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:33,614
[Beth] Alright.

137
00:09:36,951 --> 00:09:38,744
She didn't show up at her office either.

138
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,121
[sighs sharply]

139
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:43,499
[cellphone ringing]

140
00:09:44,292 --> 00:09:45,334
It's Erica.

141
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:47,003
- [ringing continues]
- Answer it.

142
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:50,965
[inhales, exhales sharply]

143
00:09:51,507 --> 00:09:53,134
Please tell me you found Mel.

144
00:10:00,933 --> 00:10:01,851
What?

145
00:10:03,686 --> 00:10:04,812
[Alice breathes shakily]

146
00:10:04,895 --> 00:10:06,522
Wait… I don't--

147
00:10:06,606 --> 00:10:08,608
I don't understand. [breath quivers]

148
00:10:08,691 --> 00:10:10,276
A severed hand?

149
00:10:11,777 --> 00:10:12,903
It was from Edong.

150
00:10:13,571 --> 00:10:14,864
[chuckles in disbelief]

151
00:10:16,157 --> 00:10:17,825
Edong sent you a…

152
00:10:18,659 --> 00:10:19,827
a hand.

153
00:10:20,703 --> 00:10:21,954
A severed hand?

154
00:10:22,538 --> 00:10:24,081
And you're saying it's…

155
00:10:25,583 --> 00:10:26,834
it's Mel's?

156
00:10:26,917 --> 00:10:28,002
[uneasy music playing]

157
00:10:28,085 --> 00:10:29,795
Edong called me.

158
00:10:29,879 --> 00:10:31,922
He didn't say it directly but,

159
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:33,841
that's what he was implying.

160
00:10:33,924 --> 00:10:35,343
[Alice] <i>No. No, no, no.</i>

161
00:10:35,426 --> 00:10:37,887
No, that… That can't be Mel's.

162
00:10:37,970 --> 00:10:39,305
[Alice breathes shakily]

163
00:10:39,388 --> 00:10:40,806
[Erica] <i>We aren't sure yet.</i>

164
00:10:41,390 --> 00:10:43,893
Right now, the crime lab's inspecting the…

165
00:10:44,852 --> 00:10:45,895
…the hand.

166
00:10:45,978 --> 00:10:49,273
<i>They're taking fingerprints</i>
<i>to compare it to their database.</i>

167
00:10:49,357 --> 00:10:51,609
- If it matches Mel's--
- [Alice]<i> No!</i>

168
00:10:51,692 --> 00:10:53,152
That isn't Mel's!

169
00:10:54,278 --> 00:10:56,030
[sighs] Please, Alice.

170
00:10:56,113 --> 00:10:57,156
[Alice] <i>That can't be.</i>

171
00:10:57,239 --> 00:10:58,449
She can't be dead!

172
00:10:58,532 --> 00:10:59,408
Give me that.

173
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:00,576
You know what? I knew it!

174
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:02,119
<i>When I saw your interview on TV,</i>

175
00:11:02,203 --> 00:11:03,913
I knew this would happen.

176
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:07,708
I only did that to direct
his attention towards me.

177
00:11:07,792 --> 00:11:10,169
I did it to protect all of you!

178
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:13,672
Well, then tell me, Attorney,
Were you able to protect Mel?!

179
00:11:14,131 --> 00:11:15,341
[exhales heavily]

180
00:11:15,424 --> 00:11:19,095
[uneasy music continues]

181
00:11:24,975 --> 00:11:27,061
[Alice breathes deeply]

182
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,023
[Beth] Damn it!

183
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:33,317
[Alice huffs]

184
00:11:33,401 --> 00:11:37,530
- [breathing loudly]
- [water trickling]

185
00:11:38,322 --> 00:11:44,745
[panicked breathing]

186
00:11:46,038 --> 00:11:49,625
[Celestino] <i>Can you tell</i>
<i>us if that was Louisa's watch?</i>

187
00:11:54,130 --> 00:11:55,172
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

188
00:11:56,298 --> 00:11:58,134
<i>This is Louisa's watch.</i>

189
00:11:59,593 --> 00:12:01,387
[young Beth] <i>What's your problem, Erica?!</i>

190
00:12:01,470 --> 00:12:02,972
<i>You lied!</i>

191
00:12:03,055 --> 00:12:05,891
<i>We all know</i>
<i>that that wasn't Louisa's watch!</i>

192
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:07,393
<i>Wow! Slay, Ma!</i>

193
00:12:07,476 --> 00:12:09,103
<i>- Me?</i>
<i>- Yes, Ma!</i>

194
00:12:09,186 --> 00:12:12,189
<i>You don't let any</i>
<i>wrongdoing slide no matter what.</i>

195
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:16,068
<i>No wonder you were friends</i>
<i>with Louisa and Attorney Erica.</i>

196
00:12:18,028 --> 00:12:22,283
[uneasy music continues, fades]

197
00:12:23,617 --> 00:12:25,369
Edong won't come near me.

198
00:12:25,953 --> 00:12:28,164
You can pull out the cops
staking out the condo.

199
00:12:28,789 --> 00:12:30,166
[Marco] Have some water first.

200
00:12:30,958 --> 00:12:33,085
After everything that happened earlier,

201
00:12:33,169 --> 00:12:35,629
Edong must've figured out
you're monitoring my location.

202
00:12:35,713 --> 00:12:39,425
You should just focus
your resources to hunt him down.

203
00:12:42,970 --> 00:12:46,307
All I ask for is security detail

204
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:47,808
at least once a week

205
00:12:48,517 --> 00:12:50,352
to ease the other residents' worries.

206
00:12:50,811 --> 00:12:51,937
Alright, Chief.

207
00:12:52,271 --> 00:12:53,272
Thank you.

208
00:12:57,943 --> 00:13:00,237
I need to review Louisa's case.

209
00:13:01,405 --> 00:13:04,200
I've gone through it countless times

210
00:13:04,533 --> 00:13:06,035
these past few days,

211
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:08,996
but I feel like I'm missing something.

212
00:13:09,079 --> 00:13:10,581
I'm forgetting some important detail.

213
00:13:11,540 --> 00:13:15,127
I've been trying to remember everything,
but my memory is failing me!

214
00:13:15,544 --> 00:13:17,129
- [huffs]
- Save it for later.

215
00:13:17,588 --> 00:13:19,298
- No, no.
- Have some rest first.

216
00:13:19,381 --> 00:13:21,008
I don't need rest!

217
00:13:22,676 --> 00:13:26,597
- [breathing heavily]
- [unsettling music playing]

218
00:13:31,018 --> 00:13:32,728
What am I missing?

219
00:13:33,938 --> 00:13:37,691
[Marco] Look, your friend might be dead.

220
00:13:37,775 --> 00:13:40,945
If you need a reason to take a break…

221
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:43,489
this is it.

222
00:13:43,572 --> 00:13:47,201
[unsettling music continues]

223
00:13:50,329 --> 00:13:55,876
[music becomes pensive]

224
00:14:09,598 --> 00:14:15,271
[pensive music continues, fades]

225
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:18,399
- [club music playing]
<i>- Dude, you know what?</i>

226
00:14:18,482 --> 00:14:20,609
<i>What the heck? She left me for that man!</i>

227
00:14:20,693 --> 00:14:23,195
<i>That guy drives a freaking Civic, bro.</i>

228
00:14:23,279 --> 00:14:26,740
<i>You know what,</i>
<i>a Porsche is just my regular car.</i>

229
00:14:27,366 --> 00:14:29,910
<i>He's probably… bigger than you.</i>

230
00:14:29,994 --> 00:14:31,495
[laughter]

231
00:14:32,079 --> 00:14:34,832
[woman cackles]

232
00:14:34,915 --> 00:14:37,042
<i>Dude, I think I know that laugh.</i>

233
00:14:37,126 --> 00:14:38,377
<i>It sounds familiar.</i>

234
00:14:39,378 --> 00:14:41,422
- [cackling continues]
<i>- Hey! Hey, Jen!</i>

235
00:14:41,505 --> 00:14:44,174
<i>- Jen, hey! Come here!</i>
<i>- Oh! Well, hello!</i>

236
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:47,803
<i>Welcome to my office hours!</i>

237
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:49,805
<i>What's up? Who's with you?</i>

238
00:14:49,889 --> 00:14:51,056
<i>I'm with a friend,</i>

239
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:53,225
<i>But, just a warning, guys. Hands off.</i>

240
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:57,855
<i>She's already married</i>
<i>to non other than Anton Montenegro.</i>

241
